solution: class Solution {
public:
    int makeTheIntegerZero(int num1, int num2) {
        long long n = num1;
        long long m = num2;
        for (int k = 1; k <= 60; ++k) {
            long long target = n - m * 1LL * k;
            if (target < 0) continue;
            if (__builtin_popcountll(target) <= k && k <= target) return k;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(60)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterate k from 1 to 60; for each k compute target = num1 - k*num2. If target is non-negative and the bit-count of target is ≤ k and k ≤ target, then k operations suffice. The constraints guarantee 60 iterations are enough.

